========================
BUILD OUTPUT DESCRIPTION
========================

In Java application project that has a main class, the IDE
automatically copies all of the JAR
files on the projects classpath to  projects dist/lib folder. The IDE
also adds each of the JAR files to the Class-Path element in the application
JAR files manifest file (MANIFEST.MF).

To run the project from the sunlab command line, go to the dist folder and
type the following:

java -jar "mmh318.jar"
